HEADWORD: Reluctate
<hw>Re*luc"tate</hw> <pr>(-t?t)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Reluct</er>.]</ety> <def>To struggle against anything; to resist; to
oppose.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧To delude their
<xex>reluctating</xex> consciences.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Dr. H.
More.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reluctation</ent>⟦br⟧
